{"word":"ληίζομαι","slug":"ληίζομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ληίζομαι</b></el> <el>(ληίζομαι,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ληίς'><el>ληίς</el></a>\n<p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a>:<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to seize as booty, to carry off as prey</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—generally, <i>to get by force, to gain, get</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to plunder, despoil</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> by raids or forays, <el>ἀλλήλους</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to plunder</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>λέλῃσμαι</el> in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <i>to be carried off, taken as booty</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}